{
  "texts": [
    "ChatGLM and ERNIE Bot performed similarly well to ChatGPT on Q1 and Q2.",
    "Nonetheless, when subjected to the inducive task of story writing, 68% and 100% of their stories contained malicious content that violates moral laws.",
    "ChatGPT, however, conformed to moral norms in 60% of the cases, though it still offered specific descriptions and methods of beating people in 40% of the cases, posing ethical risks of assisting malicious behavior and demonstrating inconsistent virtue.",
    "This indicates that while LLMs are capable of addressing moral questions and dilemmas, they may fail to recognize the prompter's malicious intention.",
    "Second, ChatGPT could provide self-consistent answers to complex moral dilemmas in a more stable manner than ChatGLM and ERNIE Bot (Table 10)."
  ]
}